  "notes": {
    "axis_index_offset": "UR3e axes are 0-indexed (0-5); voraus-AD axes are 1-indexed (1-6). Axis N maps to N+1.",
    "effort_current_vs_motor_iq": "UR3e effort_current_{axis} (actual_current, phase RMS) is mapped to motor_iq_{axis} (torque-forming current Iq) as the closest available signal. These are not identical: Iq is the torque-producing component of phase current in field-oriented control.",
    "main_voltage_broadcast": "UR3e main_voltage is a single global DC bus measurement. voraus-AD supply_voltage is repeated per axis. The single UR3e value should be broadcast to all six voraus-AD supply_voltage columns.",
    "fault_label_split": "UR3e fault_label encodes both whether an anomaly is present and its type. It maps to voraus-AD anomaly (bool: 0=normal, 1=anomalous) and category (int: anomaly type code). See the faults table for the encoding.",
    "timestamp_units": "UR3e timestamp_ms is in milliseconds; voraus-AD time is in seconds. Divide by 1000 on conversion.",
    "sample_column": "voraus-AD sample is a per-recording episode ID with no direct equivalent in the UR3e row-level schema. It must be assigned externally from episode-level metadata (e.g. episode_id).",
    "phase_mapping": "voraus-AD encodes motion stages in the 'action' column (uint8, 0-14). Odd values are active motions; even values are idle/settle between motions. action=4 (idle between descend and close) is labelled as phase 2 'settle' because its role matches the UR3e 'brief hold before grasping' description. UR3e phases 8 (retract) and 9 (return) have no active-motion equivalent in voraus-AD and therefore cannot be derived from this column."
  },
